+## 2. Binding Design Rules (Effective Immediately)
+
+The following rules apply to all new code added from v0.2.0 onward:
+
+1. No hard-coded filesystem paths outside CLI/config layers.
+2. Plotting functions must accept matplotlib Axes objects and must not
+   perform data loading or aggregation.
+3. NetCDF loading must be isolated in a dedicated I/O layer.
+4. Diagnostics must return data objects (xarray.Dataset, dict), never plots.
+5. Aggregation logic must not be duplicated across modules.
+
+Violations should be treated as technical debt and documented explicitly.
+
